The Wagner group is a private military company, controlled by the Kremlin. Russia deployed the mercenary group to eastern Ukraine after its army suffered heavy losses, the UK Ministry of Defence reported in March. However, Ukrainian forces were able to strike their base in Kadiivka and kill between 50 and 200 mercenaries (based on different estimates) after they gave themselves away by telling locals they were musicians. Oleh, a local resident said: "Wagner mercenaries don’t know how to keep their mouths shut. “They themselves went around and introduced themselves as ‘an orchestra’ or ‘musicians'." FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES...